messageBody:
Creative teaching method I must say. Though for the scheme you use I
would recommend using the Shavian alphabet minus the Vowel+r
ligatures. It has a symbol for the (*) vowel you show.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "peter_r_guinness" <malt99@...>
wrote:
>
> Hello, I have created some quickscript reading exercises/tutorials
> based on the book "Alice in Wonderland". More tutorials yet to come.
> Available here:
> http://members.optusnet.com.au/~malt99/project_quickscript_website
>
